# Build-context allowlist: the Docker daemon only receives the files the image
# actually needs. Everything is excluded by default, so stray files can never
# enter the build even if a COPY is later broadened — secrets (.env with the
# Cloudflare Tunnel token), VCS history (.git), local scratch/logs, tests,
# tooling, and docs all stay out of the image.
#
# When the Dockerfile needs a NEW path, add a matching "!" line below.

# Exclude everything...
*

# ...then re-include exactly what the Dockerfile COPYs into the image.
!index.html
!favicon.svg
!nginx.conf
!css
!js
!icons
!sw.js
!manifest.json
